HEADWORD: Ureter
<hw>U*re"ter</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/. See <er>Urine</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The duct
which conveys the urine from the kidney to the bladder or cloaca. There
are two ureters, one for each kidney.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ureteritis</ent>⟦br⟧
